---

<DocLayout
  title="formatJustifyCenter"
  description="How formatJustifyCenter inputType applies center alignment and varies across browsers."
  currentPath={Astro.url.pathname}
>
        <DocSection id="overview" title="Overview">
          <p class="m-0 mb-4">
            The <code class="bg-bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-[0.85em]">formatJustifyCenter</code> inputType is triggered when the user applies center alignment to selected paragraphs. The browser sets <code class="bg-bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-[0.85em]">text-align: center</code> on the affected elements.
          </p>
        </DocSection>

        <DocSection id="basic-behavior" title="Basic Behavior">
          <DocInfoBox title="Scenario: Paragraph selected">
            <div class="space-y-4">
              <div>
                <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold mb-2 text-text-primary">Before (Paragraph selected)</h4>
                <div class="bg-bg-surface border border-border-light rounded-md p-3 font-mono text-sm">
                  <div class="text-text-secondary">HTML:</div>
                  <div class="text-text-primary mt-1">&lt;p&gt;<span class="bg-yellow-200 dark:bg-yellow-900/40">This is a paragraph.</span>&lt;/p&gt;</div>
                </div>
              </div>
              
              <div>
                <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold mb-2 text-text-primary">After formatJustifyCenter</h4>
                <div class="bg-bg-surface border border-border-light rounded-md p-3 font-mono text-sm">
                  <div class="text-text-secondary">HTML:</div>
                  <div class="text-text-primary mt-1">&lt;p style="text-align: center;"&gt;<span class="bg-yellow-200 dark:bg-yellow-900/40">This is a paragraph.</span>&lt;/p&gt;</div>
                  <div class="text-text-secondary mt-2 text-xs">Text aligned to center</div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </DocInfoBox>
        </DocSection>

        <DocSection id="editor-specific-handling" title="Editor-Specific Handling">
          <p class="m-0 mb-4">
            Different editor frameworks handle text alignment similarly. Here's how major editors implement formatJustifyCenter:
          </p>

          <EditorExample
            editor="slate"
            title="Center Alignment"
            description="Slate applies alignment as a block property:"
            code={`import { Editor, Transforms, Element } from 'slate';

element.addEventListener('beforeinput', (e) => {
  if (e.inputType === 'formatJustifyCenter') {
    e.preventDefault();
    Transforms.setNodes(editor, {
      align: 'center',
    }, {
      match: n => Element.isElement(n) && Editor.isBlock(editor, n),
    });
  }
});`}
            features={[
              '<strong>Block property:</strong> Alignment is stored as a property on block elements.',
              '<strong>Transforms.setNodes:</strong> Sets <code class="bg-bg-surface px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-[0.85em]">align: \'center\'</code> on selected blocks.',
            ]}
          />

          <EditorExample
            editor="prosemirror"
            title="Center Alignment"
            description="ProseMirror uses block attribute:"
            code={`view.dom.addEventListener('beforeinput', (e) => {
  if (e.inputType === 'formatJustifyCenter') {
    e.preventDefault();
    const { state, dispatch } = view;
    const { $from } = state.selection;
    const blockType = schema.nodes.paragraph;
    const tr = state.tr.setBlockType($from.before(), $from.after(), blockType, {
      ...blockType.attrs,
      align: 'center',
    });
    dispatch(tr);
  }
});`}
            features={[
              '<strong>Block attribute:</strong> Alignment is stored as an attribute on block nodes.',
            ]}
          />

          <EditorExample
            editor="draftjs"
            title="Center Alignment"
            description="Draft.js uses block-level styles:"
            code={`function handleJustifyCenter(editorState) {
  return RichUtils.toggleBlockType(editorState, 'center');
}`}
            features={[
              '<strong>Block type:</strong> Uses block type for alignment.',
            ]}
          />
        </DocSection>

